sources.title: Park Avenue Logger
sources.description: Millioniare Curran (Lloyd Ingraham), thinking his son (George O'Brien) too intellectual, sends him west to learn logging at one of his lumber camps. Unknown to his father, Grant Curan is a professional wrestler and easily able to handle the thugs that attack him at the lumber camp. This enables him to stay on the job and he soon reveals how his father is being cheated by the local boss.

sources.title: Park Avenue Logger (1937) GEORGE O'BRIEN
sources.description:
Stars: George O'Brien, Beatrice Roberts, Ward Bond
 Director: David Howard

A wealthy, aristocratic, thinking his son is a pansy, sends him to work in a lumber camp. Unbeknownst to the father, the boy is already a famous wrestler known as The Masked Marvel! At camp, the young man exposes two shady foremen, and saves the logging operation of a pretty girl who falls madly in love with him!!
